    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "CliffordState[{vec1, vec2, ...}] represents a quantum state of qubits \
stabilized by the generators gk corresponding to full Gottesman vectors veck \
in {vec1, vec2, ...}. CliffordState[{s1, s2, ...}, n] returns a CliffordState \
object corresponding to the computational basis state Ket[{s1, s2, ...}] of n \
qubits. If the bit string {s1, s2, ...} is shorter (or longer) than n, then \
the bit values are cyclically repeated (or the list is simply cut).", 
    "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "CliffordState", 
